jobs_results.description:
How would you like to work in IT, toying with cutting edge technologies and enjoying your life? At Orange Services, it’s possible!

As one of the largest IT Hub within Orange Group, we are working internationally for both Orange corporate functions and country operations. Through a unique combination of know-how and expertise, our teams provide a broad range of IT & Business Solutions.

Come closer to #LifeAtOrange!

What we’re looking for:

We’re eager to bring the best senior iOS developer by our side! Can you make IT happen? Take the opportunity to boost your career in iOS development and work with some cool iOS native features. Share your passion about IT Innovation with us. We will offer you a dynamic environment where you can experience a large variety of new frameworks, while working in the most advanced Agile frameworks. Become our colleague in our mobile development team. You will contribute in building a management platform for Orange countries where My Orange corporate solution is a self-care application that offers personalized account management experience for customers in different countries. The main technologies we are using: SwiftUI and Combine, Swift, Fastlane and GitLab If you are willing to know more, we are happy to invite you for an interview.

What you’ll be doing:
• Assess, design, develop, integrate, test, and document software features with a strong focus on iOS platforms with complex business features;
• Create and maintain native packages to integrate features in My Orange country solutions;
• Code developing in SwiftUI (must have), Swift, Combine;
• Troubleshoot software issues and fix bugs;
• Participate actively and proactively in all project overviews and team meetings;
• Ownership of technical designs, code development and component test execution to demonstrate alignment to the functional specification;
• Using configuration management and integration/build automation tools to lead and deploy Xcode archives via Fastlane;
• Performing code reviews and providing critical suggestions for fixes and improvements;
• Unit testing applications using XCTest framework;
• Developing and demonstrating a broad set of technology skills in SwifUI, Combine and open-source libraries and frameworks, and technology architecture concepts;
• Collaborating within a project team with diverse and complementary skills.

What you need to know/have:
• 5+ years of experience as a software engineer building shipping iOS applications using Swift and SwiftUI;
• Eagerness to learn innovative technologies;
• Excellent understanding of object-oriented and MVVM design pattern;
• JSON and REST APIs knowledge;
• Experience with Unit and UI testing; Experience with continuous integration (Fastlane) and code versioning (GitLab);
• Experience with data obfuscation and application security;
• Very good understanding about threads and application lifecycle;
• Able to create reusable code and write technical documentation;
• Strong experience with project configuration and frameworks management;
• Focused on design details, knowledge to interact with design tools (Zeplin);
• Experience with publishing native applications in Appstore;
• Excellent communication skills in English.

What’s in it for you:
• Performance Bonuses – based on your results & the company’s;
• Loyalty Bonuses, if you extend your stay;
• Electronic Meal Tickets - as you imagine;
• Medical & Life insurance for you - facilities for your family, too;
• #WFH & Flexible hours;
• Professional GSM subscription;
• Personal GSM subscription, also [because we believe in communication!];
• Special grants on Smartphones & devices; discounts for Orange products & services;
• Development Platforms - Orange Learning, Trainings, Career Counselling, Coaching & Career plan mentoring;
• Wellbeing Programs – we support your Zen;

Orange Services is about bringing together people and technology.

Come & work for a #TopEmployer company. You could be part of an organization where great colleagues and team spirit support your professional development.

Apply and let’s have a remote-talk.

At Orange, you can.

We encourage all candidate profiles, regardless of gender, age, race, citizenship, ethnicity, color, language, religion, social origin, genetic traits, sexual orientation, permanent or temporary disability, nationality, political choice, social category or social origins, situation or family responsibility, belonging to a disadvantaged category, membership or trade union activity.
